'''Marko Jevtović''' ({{lang-sr-cyr|Марко Јевтовић}}; born 24 July 1993) is a [[Serbs|Serbian]] [[Association football|football]] [[midfielder]] who plays for [[Konyaspor]] in Turkish [[Süper Lig]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.srbijafudbal.net/novi%20pazar/jevtovic_m.htm |title=Marko Jevtović |website=srbijafudbal.net|language=Serbian|accessdate=25 April 2014}}</ref>

==Club career==

===Early career===
He started playing in esteemed youth ranks of [[FK Zemun|Zemun]]. At the age of 18 he joined [[FC Dynamo Moscow|Dynamo Moscow]], after playing a portion of 2010/2011 season for [[FK Srem Jakovo|Srem Jakovo]]. After a brief spell in Russia's capital, he returned to [[Serbia]], in Sopot. At the age of 19, he signed for [[FK Hajduk Kula|Hajduk Kula]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sportske.net/vest/domaci-fudbal/hajduk-sve-jaci-110860.html |title=Hajduk sve jači!|website=sportske.net|language=Serbian|date=13 January 2013|accessdate=25 April 2014}}</ref> Due to rather severe financial issues, the club, that excelled during the latter stages of 2012/2013 Superliga season, ceased to exist.

===Novi Pazar===
Jevtović therefore had to move again, so he left for [[FK Novi Pazar|Novi Pazar]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sportske.net/vest/domaci-fudbal/devet-hajduka-za-novi-pazar-139802.html |title=Devet 'Hajduka' za 'Novi' Pazar! |website=sportske.net|language=Serbian|date=4 August 2013|accessdate=25 April 2014}}</ref> He made his first official debut for Novi Pazar on 17 August 2013, against [[FK Rad|Rad]]. In the 2013/14 season he played 18 matches (17 in [[Serbian SuperLiga]] and 1 in [[Serbian Cup]]), but did not achieve a single goal. On 29 September 2014, he scored his first goal for Novi Pazar against [[FK Jagodina|Jagodina]] in a 3–0 home win.<ref>[http://fknovipazar.rs/2014/09/jevtovic-ukrasio-slavlje/ Jevtović ukrasio slavlje]{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} at fknovipazar.rs, 29-9-2014</ref> It was also the most beautiful goal of the season 2014/15 in the Serbian Superliga.<ref>[http://www.telegraf.rs/sport/1246029-novopazarski-ronaldo-pogledajte-gol-kola-mozda-i-polusezone-u-srpskom-fudbalu-video NOVOPAZARSKI RONALDO: Pogledajte gol kola, možda i polusezone u srpskom fudbalu! (VIDEO)] at telegraf.rs, 30-9-2014</ref> On 4 April 2015, he has scored from the penalty spot against the [[Red Star Belgrade]] in a 2–1 home win.<ref>[http://www.mozzartsport.com/vesti/zvezdin-crni-pazar-umesto-bodova-crvenobeli-brojali-promasaje-i-prvi-put-izgubila-od-plavih-video/101861 Zvezdin crni pazar: Umesto bodova crveno-beli brojali promašaje i prvi put izgubili od Plavih! (VIDEO)] at mozzartsport.com, 4-4-2015</ref> In the 28th round of Serbian SuperLeague, he scored from penalty spot against [[FK Voždovac|Voždovac]] on 13 May 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://mondo.rs/a794523/Sport/Fudbal/Superliga-28.-kolo-borba-za-opstanak-UZIVO-Spartak-Donji-Srem-Novi-Pazar-Vozdovac-Radnicki-Borac.html |title=U Subotici penal u 94, protest, tuča... |website=mondo.rs|language=Serbian|date=13 May 2015|accessdate=24 August 2015}}</ref> 2014/15 season he finished with 28 appearances and 3 goals in Novi Pazar.

===Partizan===
====2015–16 season====
Jevtović signed a four-year deal with [[FK Partizan|Partizan]] on 3 June 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.zurnal.rs/fudbal/partizan/19609/jevtovic-potpisao-cetvorogodisnji-ugovor-igranje-u-partizanu-cast-i-obaveza|title=Јевтовић потписао четворогодишњи уговор: Играње у Партизану част и обавеза!|website=[[Sportski žurnal]]|language=Serbian|date=4 June 2015|accessdate=4 June 2015}}</ref> He was handed the number 21 shirt, previously worn by [[Saša Marković (footballer, born 1991)|Saša Marković]] who played at the same position as Jevtović. Jevtović playing style reminds on former Partizan player, [[Radosav Petrović]] and many compare him to him.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mozzartsport.com/vesti/novi-raca-petrovic-stigao-u-humsku-sutiracu-penal-koji-ce-nas-odvesti-u-ligu-sampiona/107624|title=Novi Raća Petrović stigao u Humsku: Šutiraću penal koji će nas odvesti u Ligu šampiona|website=mozzartsport.com|language=Serbian|date=4 June 2015|accessdate=9 August 2015}}</ref> He made his first official debut for Partizan on 14 July 2015, against [[FC Dila Gori|Dila Gori]] in the first leg of second round qualification for [[UEFA Champions League]]. Jevtović made his [[Serbian SuperLiga|league]] debut against [[FK Metalac Gornji Milanovac|Metalac]] in a 4–0 home win on 17 July 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sr.partizan.rs/112136-partizan-spartak/|title=Partizan – Metalac 4:0 (3:0)|website=FK Partizan.rs|language=Serbian|date=17 July 2015|accessdate=17 July 2015}}</ref> Jevtović scored the equalizer against [[FC Steaua București|Steaua București]] in third round qualification for UEFA Champions League in a 4–2 home win.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.b92.net/sport/fudbal/vesti.php?yyyy=2015&mm=08&dd=05&nav_id=1023906|title=Preokret Partizana za plej-of i Evropu!|website=b92.net|language=Serbian|date=5 August 2015|accessdate=9 August 2015}}</ref> Jevtović was sent off in injury time of first half on 18 August 2015 at [[Borisov Arena]] in a play-off round of UEFA Champions League against [[FC BATE Borisov|BATE Borisov]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.telegraf.rs/sport/1709482-da-li-je-jevtovic-dobio-prestrogo-drugi-zuti-karton-video|title=Da li je Jevtović dobio prestrogo drugi žuti karton? (VIDEO)|website=telegraf.rs|language=Serbian|date=18 August 2015|accessdate=27 August 2015}}</ref> He played five matches in the [[2015–16 UEFA Europa League group stage]], against [[Athletic Bilbao]], [[AZ Alkmaar|AZ]] and [[FC Augsburg|Augsburg]]. He played the vast majority of his team's games in the first part of the [[2015–16 FK Partizan season|2015–16 season]], but in the second under newly appointed manager [[Ivan Tomić]], he spent on the bench. He helped Partizan to win the [[2015–16 Serbian Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.sr.partizan.rs/138205-138205/ | title=Kup je naš! | language=Serbian | publisher=partizan.rs | date=11 May 2016 | accessdate=14 September 2016}}</ref> 

====2016–17 season====
At the start of the [[2016–17 FK Partizan season|2016–17 season]], he was not in the protocol in several matches. Jevtović played his first match in the new season, on 11 September and provide assist in a 2–0 away league victory over [[FK Borac Čačak|Borac Čačak]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.alo.rs/miletic-i-mihajlovic-vodili-partizan-do-pobede-u-cacku/70551 | title=MAT U TRI MINUTA Miletić i Mihajlović vodili Partizan do pobede u Čačku | language=Serbian | publisher=alo.rs | date=11 September 2016 | accessdate=25 May 2017}}</ref> He played the vast majority of his team's games in the first part of the 2016–17 season. On 13 April, Jevtović scored his first goal for Partizan in SuperLiga, in a 3–1 away victory, over his former club, [[FK Novi Pazar|Novi Pazar]].<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://mondo.rs/a999487/Sport/Fudbal/UZIVO-Novi-Pazar-Partizan.html | title=Partizan po navici - "iz keca u dva" | language=Serbian | publisher=mondo.rs | date=13 April 2017 | accessdate=25 May 2017}}</ref> On 21 May, he scored his second goal in the season, in a 5–0 home win over [[FK Mladost Lučani|Mladost Lučani]] and helping club to win 27th title.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.b92.net/sport/fudbal/vesti.php?yyyy=2017&mm=05&dd=21&nav_id=1262954 | title=Partizan "petardom" do 27. titule! | language=Serbian | publisher=[[B92]] | date=21 May 2017 | accessdate=25 May 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=http://mondo.rs/a1010070/Mondo-TV/Sport/Marko-Jevtovic-gol-na-Partizan-Mladost-2-0-VIDEO.html | title=Sve je sam uradio - Jevtović, bomba! (VIDEO) | language=Serbian | publisher=mondo.rs | date=21 May 2017 | accessdate=25 May 2017}}</ref>

==International career==
Jevtović was called by coach [[Slavoljub Muslin]] in the [[Serbia national football team]] in January 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fss.rs/index.php?id=2021&aid=11778|title=Селектор Славољуб Муслин позвао 18 играча за дуел против САД у Сан Дијегу, 29. јануара|website=[[Football Association of Serbia]]|language=Serbian|date=17 January 2017|accessdate=17 January 2017}}</ref> On 29 January 2017, Jevtović made his international debut for the [[Serbia national football team]] in a friendly match against [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]] in a 0–0 away draw in [[San Diego]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.b92.net/sport/fudbal/vesti.php?yyyy=2017&mm=01&dd=30&nav_id=1225325|title=Remi Srbije sa SAD, superligaši položili test|website=[[B92]]|language=Serbian|date=29 January 2017|accessdate=30 January 2017}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Marko's older brother, Luka, is a [[journalist]], and a football analysing specialist. He works on the [[Radio Television of Serbia]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://noizz.rs/intervju/lukine-analize-mundijala-su-osvezenje-kakvo-smo-godinama-cekali/lk53mfv|title=Lukine analize Mundijala su osveženje kakvo smo godinama čekali|website=noizz.rs|language=Serbian|date=3 July 2018|accessdate=3 July 2018}}</ref>

